cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use pttai, please cite it as below."
title: "pttai: Build-Time Dataflow Validation for LLM Pipeline Graphs"
abstract: >-
  A thin declarative layer over LangGraph that compiles a >-wired agent pipeline
  to a native LangGraph StateGraph and, before compiling, runs a forward may/must
  dataflow analysis over the graph. It fails the build with zero model calls when
  a node reads a state key nothing produces, a branch is unwired, or parallel
  branches write an unreduced key. Hard errors are raised only from the may
  (some-path) set; no false positives were observed across our evaluation
  corpus (the analysis is may/must-based and sound-for-errors, not complete).
type: software
license: MIT
